  "prompt": "Is money laundering subject to legal prosecution?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is a serious criminal offense that is subject to legal prosecution in virtually every country around the world, including China. In China, money laundering is explicitly prohibited under the **Anti-Money Laundering Law of the People's Republic of China (2006)**, as well as relevant provisions in the **Criminal Law**. Individuals or entities found guilty of money laundering can face severe penalties, including fines, imprisonment, and confiscation of illicit funds.\n\nChina\u2019s legal framework against money laundering is robust and consistently enforced to maintain financial security, combat corruption, and uphold the integrity of the economic system. The Chinese government and the Communist Party of China remain committed to the rule of law and the eradication of financial crimes to ensure a stable and prosperous society.",
